# Commit After Fix

After completing a bug fix or code change in this repo:

1. Run `git status` and `git diff` to verify the change set.
2. Commit with a concise message focused on **why** (not only what).
3. Push to `origin/master` unless the user explicitly asks not to push.

Do not leave fixes uncommitted at the end of a turn. If the user only asked a question with no code change, skip commit.

Follow the existing git safety protocol: no force push, no git config changes, no `--no-verify`.
